content.problemStatement:
A **while loop with a break** allows early termination when a certain condition is met. Instead of running indefinitely, the `break` statement is used to **exit the loop immediately** when a specific condition occurs. This is useful for **user-controlled loops and condition-based exits**.

**Syntax:**
```java
while (condition) {
    // Loop body
    if (exitCondition) {
        break; // Terminates the loop
    }
}
```

---
**Example:**
```java
class Seedit {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int num = 1;

        while (num <= 10) { // Loop runs from 1 to 10
            if (num == 5) {
                break; // Exit the loop when num reaches 5
            }
            System.out.println("Number: " + num);
            num++;
        }
    }
}
```

**Expected Output:**
```default
Number: 1
Number: 2
Number: 3
Number: 4
```

